<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d53b7c5f9b5f5557b9082face9b632a0?s=50"></div><header><strong>[Pitch] Adding a Self type name shortcut for static member access</strong> from <string>Dave Abrahams</string> &lt;dabrahams at apple.com&gt;<p>April  6, 2016 at 09:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>on Wed Apr 06 2016, &quot;Bernd Ohr (jazzbox) via swift-evolution&quot; &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br></p><p>&gt; I am using a typealias for this:<br>&gt;<br>&gt; struct MyStruct {<br>&gt;     private typealias _Self = MyStruct<br>&gt;<br>&gt;     static func staticMethod() { print(&quot;staticMethod&quot;) }<br>&gt;<br>&gt;     func instanceMethod() {<br>&gt;         _Self.staticMethod()<br>&gt;     }<br>&gt; }<br></p><p>Yes, you can do that.  It&#39;s cumbersome, and you can&#39;t use your private<br>typealias in any public method signatures.<br></p><p>&gt;&gt; &gt; On Apr 5, 2016, at 4:17 PM, Timothy Wood&lt;tjw at me.com(mailto:tjw at me.com)&gt;wrote:<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; <br>&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; On Apr 5, 2016, at 3:04 PM, Joe Groff via swift-evolution&lt;swift-evolution at swift.org(mailto:swift-evolution at swift.org)&gt;wrote:<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; What you&#39;re describing should be spelled `Self`, IMO. I think<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; Tim intended `#Self` to mean the *static* type the code is<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; declared inside (which is the same as Self unless you&#39;re in a<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; class).<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; <br>&gt;&gt; &gt; Yes, that is what I was aiming for. `#Self` would be a pretty much<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; textual replacement just like #file, etc. That is, I could imaging<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; it being used in a bunch of cases (not useful here, but just<br>&gt;&gt; &gt; intending to enumerate the possible uses I see):<br>&gt;&gt; Please check to ensure that the changes I just made match your expectations:<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; https://